interactions.lmstext: 2. The plane enclosed by A is the ____________ _____________.
3. The ________ _________ form the anterolateral borders of the pelvic outlet.
4. Identify ligament A.
5. Identify muscle A.
6. The measurement of the distance between the sacral promontory and top of the pubis symphysis is called the __________ ____________.
7. The urogenital and anal triangles are separated by the ______________ line.
8. The muscular roof of the perineum is the _____________ _____________.
9. The region immediately superior to the perineal membrane is the _________ _________ ___________.
10. The _________ ___________ is a knot of connective tissue located between the urogenital hiatus and the opening for the anal canal.
11. The perineal spaces lateral to the anal canal are the _________ ___________.
12. The _________ ___________ ___________ forms the floor of the anterior recesses of the ischioanal fossae.
13. The superficial perineal pouch is limited superiorly by the ________ _________.
14. The space between the labia minora is called the _____________.
15. The female homologue of the corpus spongiosum are the _____________ of the ______________. (two words, separated by one space)
16. The female homologue of the bulbourethral glands are the _____________ ______________ glands.
17. Which are skeletal muscle of the superficial perineal pouch? Choose all that apply.
18. What fibre types are present in the pudendal nerve? Choose all that apply.
19. Which of the following nerves carry parasympathetic fibres responsible for erection?

choices.lmstext: dorsal nerve of the penis / clitoris
